== Crispy Potato & Zucchini ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise;
cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.

Toss potatoes and zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

== Cilantro Crema ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan crema{4%tablespoon} and cilantro.
Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Once veggies are done roasting, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}
and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with roasted veggies. Top with
@pico de gallo{4%ounce}(drained). Drizzle with cilantro crema and as much
@hot sauce{2%teaspoon} as you like.

Serve tacos with @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce} on the side.